whereas.text:
Whereas between 1987 and 1988, nearly 2,700,000 illegal
			 immigrants received legal status under the 1986 IRCA amnesty before being
			 granted lawful permanent residence by 1992;

Whereas IRCA contained provisions to inhibit future
			 illegal immigration by penalizing employers who knowingly hire an unauthorized
			 immigrant;

Whereas despite these penalties, a policy brief by the
			 Migration Policy Institute dated August 2005 showed that over 90 percent of
			 unauthorized males in the United States were employed;

Whereas illegal immigration actually increased in volume
			 and frequency by 1989, with 1,700,000 to 2,500,000 unauthorized immigrants
			 crossing into the United States from Mexico that year;
